# AIDIT Cursor Rules - Secrets Management

## Environment Variables & Secrets

### NEVER
- ❌ Display raw secret values in responses
- ❌ Commit `.env` files to git
- ❌ Hardcode secrets in source code
- ❌ Share secrets in chat or logs
- ❌ Use production secrets in development

### ALWAYS
- ✅ Use `.env.example` templates with placeholders
- ✅ Mask secret values when displaying (e.g., `sk_test_****...****1234`)
- ✅ Validate secrets before deployment
- ✅ Categorize secrets correctly (User vs Team)
- ✅ Keep documentation synchronized

## Secret Categories

### User Secrets (Personal)
Store in: Cursor Settings → User Secrets
- Gaming platform APIs (Steam, Xbox, PSN, Nintendo)
- Personal AI/ML API keys (OpenAI)
- Personal analytics tokens

### Team Secrets (Shared)
Store in: Cursor Settings → Team Secrets
- Database credentials (PostgreSQL)
- Redis connection strings
- Object storage keys (S3/MinIO)
- Payment processing (Stripe)
- Security keys (JWT, Session)
- Email service credentials (SMTP)
- Monitoring services (Sentry)

## Validation
Before any deployment or major change:
```bash
cd backend
python validate_secrets.py
```

